3. The Penguins file for bank-
ruptcy again — Pittsburgh
Penguins owners Roger Marino and
Howard Baldwin have piled up a
$37.5 million debt over the past two
seasons, forcing the Pens recently
to file for Chapter 11 bankruptcy
protection  again.

Marino says the only solution
now is to build another arena.
Imagine the loan officer’s reaction:
“Yeah sure, here you go, Roger.

You seem to have an excellent
credit background. Oh, wait a
minute — you have just a little too
much debt than we allow. Sorry.”

Anyway, Marino accepted $12.9

million in renovations in exchange .

for extending the Penguins’ Civic
Arena lease through 2007.

Roger, you should be grateful
that you got any money for renova-
tions.

Isn’t it time we stop building
arenas. and stadiums for these own-
ers who complain about a lack of
revenue?

It’s not the public’s responsibil-
ity to financially support these
teams. Actually, we do —- it’s called
the $65 ticket. As Vinnie Barbarino
from Welcome Back, Kotter says —
“What a gyp!”

In the end, the Pens and Marino
will probably get a new arena.
That’s the kind of demented world
we live in. How does the Mellon
Bank Money Pit sound?

I guess all I want is to have my
faith restored in sports. No, not just
in sports, but in love, life and
sports. In that order please.

I do have my priorities, you
know.

